{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17644757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17644757"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:07:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:07:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18061"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18061","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18061"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0.04,0,0.96]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10775"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75157"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10775","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10775"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18061"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60665"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5679"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25129"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25984"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75157","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75157"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman presents to the emergency department with acute appendicitis. The surgical team recommends an appendicectomy. The woman has full decision-making capacity and refuses surgery, stating she wants to try alternative medicine first.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following ethical principles is most relevant to respecting this patient\u0027s decision?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Justice","Non-maleficence","Beneficence","Veracity","Autonomy"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most relevant ethical principle in this scenario is \u003Cstrong\u003Eautonomy\u003C/strong\u003E, which refers to the right of patients with decision-making capacity to make their own healthcare choices, even if healthcare providers disagree with those choices.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe other principles are less directly relevant in this case:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBeneficence\u003C/strong\u003E (doing good) would support performing the surgery to treat the appendicitis\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-maleficence\u003C/strong\u003E (avoiding harm) could apply to both performing or not performing surgery\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJustice\u003C/strong\u003E relates to fair distribution of healthcare resources\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVeracity\u003C/strong\u003E refers to truthfulness in communication with patients\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EWhile the surgical team may believe surgery is in the patient\u0027s best interest, they must respect her autonomous decision to decline the procedure, provided she has been given appropriate information about the risks and benefits and has the capacity to make this decision.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The four core principles of medical ethics are autonomy, beneficence, non-maleficence, and justice.","Autonomy refers to the right of patients to make informed decisions about their own healthcare.","Informed consent requires disclosure of relevant information, patient capacity, and voluntary decision-making."],"references":["Mandal J, Ponnambath DK, Parija SC. Bioethics: A brief review. Trop Parasitol. 2017;7(1):5-7. doi:10.4103/tp.TP_4_17","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60665"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18061"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60665","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60665"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-29T07:50:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-29T07:51:31+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10775"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75157"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4947","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4947"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude7a","name":"Introduction to Clinical Sciences ","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":